<item>
            <title>[SOLR-694] Use SpellingQueryConverter as default if there is no queryconverter defined</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-694</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;the relevant code (org.apache.solr.handler.component.SpellCheckComponent) only checks if the size of the queryConverters map equals 1 and throws a RuntimeException with the message &quot;One and only one queryConverter may be defined&quot; if it does not.&lt;br/&gt;
But if there are no query converters defined this message is quite misleading.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use the SpellingQueryConverter as the default if none are defined in the configuration instead of a misleading error message.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12402282">SOLR-694</key>
            <summary>Use SpellingQueryConverter as default if there is no queryconverter defined</summary>
